{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17590617","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17590617"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"answeredAt":null,"options":[],"response":null,"finalizedAt":null},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15211"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17591860","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17591860"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:07:12+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:07:12+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15211"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15211","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15211"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0,0.25,0.5,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7902"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65929"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7902","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7902"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15211"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51375"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"8741"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19256"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19258"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19264"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22026"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65929"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EOn a global basis, carcinoma of the oesophagus is in the top twenty of the most prevalent cancers, with over 500,000 new cases being reported in 2022. It is a cancer with a relatively poor prognosis as it often presents at an advanced stage. One particular stage has a 5-year survival rate of 10-15%, regardless of whether surgical or medical treatment is chosen.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following stages does this most likely refer to?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Stage I","Stage II","Stage III","Stage IVA","Stage IVB"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EOesophageal carcinoma is typically diagnosed at \u003Cstrong\u003EStage IV\u003C/strong\u003E, which carries a poor prognosis with 5-year survival rates of 10-15%. At this stage, distant metastases are often present.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStage I\u003C/strong\u003E disease is confined to the mucosa or submucosa with no lymph node involvement and has a 5-year survival of about 45%. \u003Cstrong\u003EStage II\u003C/strong\u003E involves muscularis propria or adventitia invasion with limited lymph node spread and has a 5-year survival rate of about 30%. \u003Cstrong\u003EStage III\u003C/strong\u003E involves more extensive local spread or regional lymph node involvement and has 3-5 year survival rates of 20-30%. \u003Cstrong\u003EStage IVb \u003C/strong\u003Esurvival rate is less than 5%.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOesophageal cancer is staged as:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage 0     Tis     N0 M0\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage I      T1      N0 M0\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage IIA   T1      N1 M0\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage IIB    T2    N1 M0\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage III     T2-4 N1 M0\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage IVA  T1-4 N2\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStage IVB  Any T Any N M1\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhere T = primary tumour, N = nodal involvement, M = metastatic disease\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Stage IV oesophageal carcinoma is the most common presenting stage with a 5-year survival rate of 10-15%"],"references":["Wang Y, Mukkamalla SKR, Singh R, Babiker HM, Lyons S. Esophageal Cancer. 2024 Aug 17. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29083661","Codipilly DC, Wang KK. Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Esophagus. Gastroenterol Clin North Am. 2022 Sep;51(3):457-484. doi: 10.1016/j.gtc.2022.06.005. Epub 2022 Aug 29. PMID: 36153105","Hadian Y, Howell JY, Ramsey ML, et al. Cutaneous Squamous Cell Carcinoma. [Updated 2024 Jul 2]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK441939/","Burton KA, Ashack KA, Khachemoune A. Cutaneous Squamous Cell Carcinoma: A Review of High-Risk and Metastatic Disease. Am J Clin Dermatol. 2016 Oct;17(5):491-508. doi: 10.1007/s40257-016-0207-3. PMID: 27358187","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51375"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15211"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51375","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51375"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-27T17:09:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-27T17:09:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7902"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65929"}}},"meta":{"c